@page
@model McpViaApimModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Use the MCP server through Azure API Management";
    ViewData["Description"] = "Learn how to expose the Office Versions MCP endpoint through Azure API Management and call it from AI clients or custom integrations.";
}

<div class="container">
    <div class="privacy-header">
        <div class="privacy-header-icon">
            <i class="bi bi-cloud-arrow-up"></i>
        </div>
        <h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
        <p>Expose the Office Versions MCP endpoint behind Azure API Management and keep the backend routing simple.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-12">
            <div class="privacy-container">
                <div class="privacy-section">
                    <h2><i class="bi bi-info-circle me-2"></i>Overview</h2>
                    <p>
                        The Office Versions MCP server is exposed publicly through Azure API Management (APIM).
                        APIM is the front door for the endpoint, adding subscription-key authentication, rate limiting,
                        and observability without changing the backend implementation.
                    </p>
                    <div class="alert alert-info" role="alert">
                        <i class="bi bi-lightbulb me-2"></i>
                        <strong>Tip:</strong> the OpenAPI definition is available at <a href="/swagger/v1/mcp-openapi.json" target="_blank">/swagger/v1/mcp-openapi.json</a>.
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="privacy-section">
                    <h2><i class="bi bi-hdd-network me-2"></i>Public endpoint</h2>
                    <p>The MCP server is reachable at the following APIM URL:</p>
                    <pre><code>https://api.office365versions.com/office-mcp</code></pre>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>GET</strong> — returns MCP server information.</li>
                        <li><strong>POST</strong> — JSON-RPC 2.0 endpoint (<code>initialize</code>, <code>ping</code>, <code>tools/list</code>, <code>tools/call</code>).</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="privacy-section">
                    <h2><i class="bi bi-key me-2"></i>Authentication</h2>
                    <p>
                        Every request must include a subscription key in the <code>Ocp-Apim-Subscription-Key</code> header.
                        Use the public MCP key below:
                    </p>
                    <pre><code>Ocp-Apim-Subscription-Key: ef386cc43d4b40278c78fb648b9cbc59</code></pre>
                    <div class="alert alert-warning" role="alert">
                        <i class="bi bi-speedometer2 me-2"></i>
                        <strong>Rate limits:</strong> up to <strong>50 requests per day</strong> per client IP address,
                        with a short-term burst limit of 20 requests per minute. Exceeding the limits returns
                        <code>HTTP 429 Too Many Requests</code>.
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="privacy-section">
                    <h2><i class="bi bi-terminal me-2"></i>Example calls</h2>
                    <p>Retrieve MCP server information:</p>
                    <pre><code>curl https://api.office365versions.com/office-mcp \
  -H "Ocp-Apim-Subscription-Key: ef386cc43d4b40278c78fb648b9cbc59"</code></pre>

                    <p>List the available tools via JSON-RPC:</p>
                    <pre><code>curl -X POST https://api.office365versions.com/office-mcp \
  -H "Ocp-Apim-Subscription-Key: ef386cc43d4b40278c78fb648b9cbc59" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":1,"method":"tools/list"}'</code></pre>
                </div>

                <div class="privacy-section">
                    <h2><i class="bi bi-shield-check me-2"></i>Security and operational notes</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Protect the public endpoint with subscription keys, OAuth, or IP restrictions.</li>
                        <li>Use APIM policies to add rate limiting and logging for MCP traffic.</li>
                        <li>Keep the backend route at <code>/mcp</code> so the OpenAPI definition remains aligned with the implementation.</li>
                        <li>Monitor the APIM and backend logs to confirm that JSON-RPC requests are being forwarded correctly.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

@section Scripts {
    <style>
        pre {
            background-color: var(--bs-gray-100, #f8f9fa);
            border-radius: 0.5rem;
            padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
            overflow-x: auto;
        }

        code {
            font-size: 0.95rem;
        }
    </style>
}
